Class Dog

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4.Animal
      • edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4.Dog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Dog
extends Animal
    The Dog object is a subclass of Animal, so it will inherit all of it's fields and methods. The Dog will have 5 different variety's of dog type, which will help make each dog distinct.
    Author:
    David Scianni

    • Method Detail

      • vaccinationSize

        public int vaccinationSize()
        First, this method will make a temporary variable temp and make it equal to 0. Then it will check the vaccinations array, and if the ith variable is not null, it will add 1 to temp. When a null pointer is found, then it will break the for loop, and return the temp number. This temp will be how many variables are in the array that are not null.
        Returns:
        temp, which is the number of non-null variables in the array

        public void printAnimal()
        Description copied from class: Animal
        Abstract method that will print out the animals information. It is different for the Dog object because Dog has vaccinations as well. Besides that, they all print out the Owner's info, their info, and any diseases and appointments they have.
